\begin_layout Section
Methodology
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This work focuses primarily on the scheduling aspect of resource management.
 Specifically, it focuses on the resources involved in its scheduling aspect.
 It examines the important attributes and dependencies of these resources,
 and it examines the interaction and integration of the systems which manage
 them individually.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While this thesis does not concern itself directly with the problems of
 human resources, facility managment, university documentation, or any other
 aspect of resource management, it does mention them often either directly
 or tangentelly.
 This is unavoidable due to the associative nature of scheduling which binds
 resources of these different aspects to create new resource types.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
However the crux of this work is the integration of some of the various
 resource management systems which are responsible for the resources used
 in the scheduling process.
 These systems and the workflows which are responsible for the management
 of their data will be a central point of this work.
